The paper discusses a new deep multi-agent RL method for the card game Hanabi, which requires agents to reason over the intentions, beliefs, and point of view of other agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Game Theory (cs.GT), Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), and Computation and Language (cs.CL) which deal with topics related to AI, RL, game theory, multi-agent systems, and natural language processing, respectively.
